{"article_id":"pwOuhz0V2ar4D5y8","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Supreme Court ruled on Tuesday","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"that a Montana program","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"that excluded religious schools from a student aid initiative","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"violates religious freedoms","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"protected under the U.S. Constitution .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"The 5-4 majority decision ,","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"which fell along ideological lines ,","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"said","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"that","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"by making state-backed private school scholarships off-limits to parochial schools ,","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"the program ran afoul of First Amendment protections for the free exercise of religion ,","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"which prohibits the government from treating religious and secular groups differently .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"\" A state need not subsidize private education , \"","depth":5},{"id":13,"text":"Chief Justice John Roberts wrote for the majority .","depth":5},{"id":14,"text":"\" But","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"once a state decides to do so ,","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"it can not disqualify some private schools","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"solely because they are religious . \"","depth":5},{"id":18,"text":"At the center of the dispute is a 2015 tax credit program","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"the Montana legislature passed","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"to promote school choice .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"Under the plan , taxpayers could receive a dollar-for-dollar tax credit","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"by donating up to $ 150 to organizations","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"that used the donations","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"to award student scholarships to private schools .","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"But the program clashed with the so-called no aid provision of Montana ' s state Constitution .","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"That clause makes it illegal for government entities to give \" any direct or indirect appropriation or payment from any public fund or monies \" to religious organizations .","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"In 2018 , the Montana Supreme Court ruled 5-2","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"that the tax credit scheme violated the no-aid provision","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"and struck down the entire scholarship program .","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"This prompted several Montana parents of Christian school students to appeal to the U.S. Supreme Court ,","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"arguing","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"that the ruling violated the First Amendment ' s free exercise clause .","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"In their majority decision Tuesday , the justices reversed the Montana Supreme Court ruling ,","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"finding its application of the state ' s no-aid provision unconstitutional .","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"Katherine Franke , a law professor at Columbia University , said","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"the decision reflected an interpretative approach","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"that has been advanced by religious conservatives over the past two decades .","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"\" This position seeks to frame a state 's efforts","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"to maintain a wall of separation between public and religious entities as a form of discrimination against religious entities , \"","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"said Franke ,","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"who serves as faculty director of Columbia University ' s Law , Rights , and Religion Project .","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"Two of the court ' s more conservative justices","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"-- Clarence Thomas","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"Clarence ThomasSupreme Court rules","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"Booking.com can trademark name","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"Supreme Court hands win to religious schools","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"Trump 's mark on federal courts could last decades","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"MORE","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"and Neil Gorsuch","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"Neil Gorsuch","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"upreme Court hands win to religious schools","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"rump 's mark on federal courts could last decades","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"NN 's Toobin :","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"oberts 'may not be who we thought","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"e was '","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"ORE --","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"ould have gone even further","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"o advance religious rights at the state level .","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"n a concurring opinion , Thomas argued","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"hat the court ' s current treatment of the First Amendment ' s Establishment Clause ,","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"hich functions as a sort of counterweight to the free exercise clause ,","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"nduly interferes with states ' ability","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"o support religious activities .","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"So long as this hostility remains ,","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"ostered by our distorted understanding of the Establishment Clause ,","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"ree exercise rights will continue to suffer , \"","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"homas ,","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"oined by Gorsuch ,","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"rote .","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"n a fiery dissent , Justice Sonia Sotomayor","depth":6},{"id":71,"text":"onia SotomayorSupreme Court hands win to religious schools","depth":6},{"id":72,"text":"n The Money :","depth":6},{"id":73,"text":"overnors rethink opening bars , restaurants amid spike in COVID-19 cases |","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"piking cases threaten fragile economic recovery |","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"upreme Court rules","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"onsumer bureau director can be fired at will","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"upreme Court rules","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"onsumer bureau director can be fired at will","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"ORE accused the majority of using Montana ' s defunct scholarship program","depth":3},{"id":80,"text":"o supply an overly broad reading of the free exercise clause .","depth":3},{"id":81,"text":"Today ' s ruling is perverse , \"","depth":4},{"id":82,"text":"he wrote .","depth":4},{"id":83,"text":"Without any need or power","depth":5},{"id":84,"text":"o do so ,","depth":5},{"id":85,"text":"he Court appears to require a State to reinstate a tax-credit program","depth":5},{"id":86,"text":"hat the Constitution did not demand in the first place . \"","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":173,"left":165,"right":172,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":165,"left":104,"right":164,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":104,"left":98,"right":103,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":98,"left":91,"right":97,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":91,"left":0,"right":90,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":90,"left":88,"right":89,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":88,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":89,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":97,"left":93,"right":96,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":93,"left":92,"right":7,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":92,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":8,"right":95,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":95,"left":9,"right":94,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":94,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":99,"right":102,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":99,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":101,"right":17,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":14,"right":100,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":100,"lef